## Bug Found! 🐛

I discovered a **contract violation bug** in `aiogram.filters.command.CommandObject.text`. 

The property claims to "Generate original text from object" but normalizes all whitespace (tabs, multiple spaces) to single spaces, breaking the round-trip property for command parsing.

**Bug Details:**
- When parsing `/start  John` (double space), it reconstructs as `/start John` (single space)
- Affects tabs and any multiple whitespace characters
- Violates the documented contract of preserving original text

The bug report has been saved to: `bug_report_aiogram_filters_command_2025-08-18_23-07_651b.md`

**Testing Summary:**
- ✅ Tested 6 properties on CommandObject 
- ✅ All basic tests passed initially
- 🐛 Found bug when testing whitespace preservation property with Hypothesis
- 📝 Created comprehensive bug report with reproduction steps and suggested fix
